TITLE

Longer lactation duration is associated with decreased prevalence of non-alcoholic fatty liver disease in women

PARAGRAPH

A longer duration of breastfeeding has been associated with multiple potential health benefits for the mother including reduction in heart disease, diabetes and certain cancers.

In this study we found that breastfeeding for longer than 6â€¯months was associated with a lower risk of non-alcoholic fatty liver disease in mid-life.